{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-index-page-js","path":"/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Ensure every story's purpose aligns with that of the organization","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3027989821882953,"src":"/static/d81e0e6474ef7daf77e9b5ae3866f9f1/0b763/home-jumbotron.jpg","srcSet":"/static/d81e0e6474ef7daf77e9b5ae3866f9f1/89b9c/home-jumbotron.jpg 512w,\n/static/d81e0e6474ef7daf77e9b5ae3866f9f1/0b763/home-jumbotron.jpg 652w","sizes":"(max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px"}}},"heading":"Designed by scrum team, for scrum teams.","subheading":"A free jira issue visualization and storyboarding tool","mainpitch":{"title":"Why StoryPurpose","description":"As software continues to eat the world, organizations are undergoing digital transformation. In doing that it is extremely important to ensure every effort put in digital adoption is eventually aligned to the organization's purpose.\n\nStoryPurpose enables visualizing the smallest unit of deliverable (user story) in the bigger scheme of things\n"},"description":"As the backlog and the team size grows, it becomes difficult to track story breakup and prioritization. StoryPurpose provides fundamental tools to get a high level perspective of the story and how it aligns back to epic, team goals, initiative purpose, project purpose which in turn  should align back to overal organization mission.","intro":{"blurbs":[{"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.935483870967742,"src":"/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/1a97c/purposeview.png","srcSet":"/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/d32b9/purposeview.png 60w,\n/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/d08e9/purposeview.png 120w,\n/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/1a97c/purposeview.png 240w,\n/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/25c6b/purposeview.png 360w,\n/static/98c6df92693485579a94582c6da2ce44/4ce82/purposeview.png 480w","sizes":"(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px"}}},"text":"Hierarchical view of the story purpose. \n\nDepending upon the configuration, the tool provides a detailed view of the purpose of every level of the story. This makes it easier to understand if the intent of the give stories aligns all the way back to that of the organization.\n"},{"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2,"src":"/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/1a97c/storyboardview.png","srcSet":"/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/d32b9/storyboardview.png 60w,\n/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/d08e9/storyboardview.png 120w,\n/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/1a97c/storyboardview.png 240w,\n/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/25c6b/storyboardview.png 360w,\n/static/83406c94b1204cb40ab9a08eb025d1cb/4ce82/storyboardview.png 480w","sizes":"(max-width: 240px) 100vw, 240px"}}},"text":"Storyboard view of an epic.\n\nDepending upon the size of the epic and the related stories, it may not necessarily be possible to complete all stories in a single sprint or a release. Having a release-wise layout of the stories helps plan better deliveries.\n"}]}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"819b7d93-39ac-5c21-91cc-00a6f5a4a8bc"}}}